There are more than 400 minor care health clinics across the country located right inside Walgreens retail locations. They offer flu shots, drug testing and other minor care procedures. An office visit at Walgreens Take Care Clinic costs $80-$90. The prices for various treatments, procedures and testing are not included and will vary, depending on what the physician orders. 

If you're wondering how much are flu shots at Walgreens, they're about $32 per dose for ages 2 and over. There are also other flu shot alternatives at Walgreens – like the FluMist spray and FluZone. For more information, see Flu Shots at Walgreens. 

Walgreens sells over-the-counter drug testing kits that can be used at home or sent off to a manufacturer's lab for the results. Prices vary, depending on the type of test you choose - from $8 to $140. 
 Walgreens Photo Services

Prints and enlargements at Walgreens start at just $.12 each. They offer discounts on print orders up to 50% off and also have regular coupons available for their photo services as well. They also have coupons and discounts for greeting cards, print gifts, Photo gift orders, and other specialty photo products. 

Passport photos at Walgreens cost $11.99 per set and are available for same day pickup at most locations. To find out more about Walgreens Passport Photos, see How Much Are Passport Photos at Walmart?
 Other Walgreens Services

Most Walgreens locations sell full stamp booklets only. Be sure to call in advance to see if your local store is one of them. 

Walgreens carries a wide range of gift cards for department stores, restaurants and online retailers. The selection may vary between stores. They also sell select gift cards online and offer free shipping on gift card orders over $25. 
What Walgreens Coupons Exist?

Stock up on household staples and wellness items and save money with Walgreens promo codes. Most Walgreens coupon codes are for discounts on specific services, like Walgreens photo lab. During the holidays, including Black Friday and Cyber Monday, Walgreens will feature discounts for holiday decor, gifts, toys, Christmas card and a whole array of personalized photo gifts. You may also find Walgreens discounts on specific brands, like Revlon, L’Oreal or Huggies. Walgreens also sometimes offers discounts on entire product categories, like their mobility products such as canes or walkers. 

Watch the banner ads at Walgreens to find out where their current promotional offers are and the coupon codes needed to take advantage of them. Coupons change frequently with new offers added daily. Visit this Walgreens coupon page often to get the best offers during Black Friday and Cyber Monday. There are so many deals, you simply won't want to miss. If you sign up for the Walgreens email list, they will send coupon codes and promotional offers to your inbox as they become available, too. 

You can check the flyer for your local Walgreens store online via their website to find out what's on sale this week. Some online deals may be available in your local stores, too and vice versa – so be sure to ask when you shop. Be sure to check out the selection of Walgreens coupon codes at Coupons.com as well. 

To visit a Walgreens near me, find out Walgreens store locations. 
 About Walgreens

Walgreens started out as a small family owned corner pharmacy on the South Side of Chicago in 1901.Charles R. Walgreen Sr. mixed and marketed his own brand of drugs at the pharmacy to ensure quality and low prices for his customers.  By 1919, Walgreens had expanded to include a chain of 20 stores. During Prohibition when many merchants were losing money on the alcohol band, Walgreens was having great financial success because prescription whiskey was still legal – and they were the only stores that carried it. 

By 1930, Walgreens boasted nearly 400 stores across four states and annual sales of over $4 million. Over the years, the Walgreens empire continued to grow as the company changed hands within the family many times. By the 1950s, Walgreens revolutionized the way consumers shopped by introducing barcode scanning and self-serve checkout lines. 

Between 1984 and 1994, Walgreens opened a staggering 1,000 additional stores. In 1999, the company launched their website and online pharmacy and celebrated the opening of their 3,000th store the next year. Today, the Walgreens Empire includes 8,206 stores across the US. The Walgreens brand also operates several well-known Internet pharmacy brands, such as Beauty.com, Drugstore.com and VisionDirect.com. 

Beauty.com offers everything you need from haircare, skin care, makeup and more. Shop brands like Revlon, Cerave, Aveeno at discounted prices when their latest coupons. Check out our Beauty.com coupons to save instantly. 

Drugstore.com offers sales and coupons for their wide range of beauty products, haircare, household items and more. Whatever you're shopping for, be sure to use one of the many Drugstore.com coupons to save even more. 

